definition.description:
The payment table records each payment made by a customer, with information such as the amount and the rental being paid for (when applicable).

The payment table refers to the customer, rental, and staff tables.

fields.description: The amount of the payment.
fields.name: amount

fields.description: The customer whose balance the payment is being applied to. This is a foreign key reference to the customer table.
fields.name: customerId

fields.description: The date the payment was processed.
fields.name: paymentDate

fields.description: A surrogate primary key used to uniquely identify each payment.
fields.name: paymentId

fields.description: The rental that the payment is being applied to. This is optional because some payments are for outstanding fees and may not be directly related to a rental.

fields.name: staffId

definition.description:
The staff table lists all staff members, including information for email address, login information, and picture.

The staff table refers to the store and address tables using foreign keys, and is referred to by the rental, payment, and store tables.

fields.description: Whether this is an active employee. If employees leave, their rows are not deleted from this table; instead, this column is set to FALSE.
fields.name: active

fields.description: A foreign key to the staff member address in the address table.
fields.name: addressId

fields.description: The staff member email address.
fields.name: email

fields.description: The first name of the staff member.
fields.name: firstName

fields.description: The last name of the staff member.
fields.name: lastName

fields.description: When the row was created or most recently updated.
fields.name: lastUpdate

fields.description: The password used by the staff member to access the rental system. The password should be stored as a hash using the SHA2() function.
fields.name: password

fields.description: A BLOB containing a photograph of the employee.
fields.name: picture

fields.description: A surrogate primary key that uniquely identifies the staff member.
fields.name: staffId

fields.description: The staff member “home store.” The employee can work at other stores but is generally assigned to the store listed.
fields.name: storeId

fields.description: The user name used by the staff member to access the rental system.
fields.name: username

definition.description:

definition.description:
The store table lists all stores in the system. All inventory is assigned to specific stores, and staff and customers are assigned a “home store”.

The store table refers to the staff and address tables using foreign keys and is referred to by the staff, customer, and inventory tables.

fields.description: A foreign key identifying the address of this store.
fields.name: addressId

fields.description: When the row was created or most recently updated.
fields.name: lastUpdate

fields.description: A foreign key identifying the manager of this store.
fields.name: managerStaffId

fields.description: A surrogate primary key that uniquely identifies the store.
fields.name: storeId
